st: Ha [MASK] qeta lijo tsa hoseng tsa hae, o ile a ea bakeng sa letoto la leoatle. Motse o moqotetsane o moqotetsane, o khopameng oa Dover o ipata hole le lebopong, 'me oa mathela hloohong ea eona ka har'a mafika a chalk, joalo ka ostrich ea leoatle. Leoatle le ne le e-na le lehoatata la qubu ea leoatle le ba neng ba korotla ka mokhoa o fetisisang, 'me leoatle la etsa seo e neng e se rata, le seo le se ratang e ne e le timetso. E ile ea utloahala motseng, 'me ea utloahala ka mafika, 'me ea tlisa lebopong, ka bohlanya. Moea har'a matlo e ne e le oa tatso ea piscatory hoo motho a ka beng a nahana hore tlhapi e kulang e ile ea nyoloha ho kenngoa ho eona, ha batho ba kulang ba theohela ho kenngoa ka leoatleng. Ho tšoasa litlhapi tse nyane ho ne ho le boema-kepe, 'me bongata bo boholo bo pharalletseng bosiu, le ho sheba leoatleng: haholo linakong tseo ha leqhubu le entsoe, 'me le ne le le haufi le moroallo. Bahoebi ba banyenyane, ba neng ba sa etse khoebo eng kapa eng, ka linako tse ling ba ne ba sa hlokomele maruo a maholo, 'me ho ne ho makatsa hore ha ho motho ea ka mamellang lebone.
yo: Nígbà tí [MASK] ti parí oúnjẹ àárọ̀ rẹ̀ tán, ó jáde lọ fún ìyípadà ní etí òkun. Ìlú Dover kékeré tí ó tóbi, tí kò dára fi ara rẹ̀ pamọ́ kúrò ní etí òkun, ó sì sáré orí rẹ̀ sínú àpáta chalk, gẹ́gẹ́ bí ẹyẹ òkun. Etí òkun náà jẹ́ aṣálẹ̀ ọ̀pọ̀lọpọ̀ òkun àti àwọn tí wọ́n ṣubú gidigidi nípa rẹ̀, òkun sì ṣe ohun tí ó fẹ́ràn, ohun tí ó sì fẹ́ràn ni ìparun. Ó rọ̀ ní ìlú náà, ó sì mọ́lẹ̀ ní àpáta, ó sì mú etíkun sọ̀kalẹ̀, ó sì ya wèrè. Afẹ́fẹ́ tó wà láàárín àwọn ilé náà jẹ́ adùn piscatory débi pé ènìyàn lè ti rò pé ẹja aláìsàn gòkè lọ sínú rẹ̀, bí àwọn aláìsàn ṣe sọ̀kalẹ̀ láti wọ inú òkun. Ìpẹja díẹ̀ wà ní etíkun, àti ọ̀pọ̀lọpọ̀ yíyí kiri ní alẹ́, tí wọ́n sì ń wò inú òkun: pàápàá jùlọ ní àwọn àkókò wọ̀nyẹn nígbà tí ìgbì omi ṣe, ó sì súnmọ́ àkúnya omi. Àwọn oníṣòwò kéékèèké, tí wọn kò ṣe okòwò ohunkóhun, nígbà mìíràn wọ́n máa ń mọ ọrọ̀ ńlá, ó sì yani lẹ́nu pé kò sí ẹnikẹ́ni ní àdúgbò tí ó lè fara da iná fìtílà.
tn: E rile [MASK] fetsa go ja dijo tsa sefitlholo, o ne a ya go ya kwa letshitshing la lewatle. Motse o monnye o o pitlaganeng, o o kgopang o ne wa iphitlha go tswa mo lotshitshing lwa lewatle, o ne wa tabogela mo ditshimong tsa chalk, jaaka ostrich ya lewatle. Lebopo e ne e le sekaka sa diqubu tsa lewatle, mme tse di neng di tshwenya haholo, mme lewatle la etsa seo le se ratang, le seo le se ratang e ne e le tshenyo. E ne ya duma mo motseng, mme ya duma mo ditshimong, ya ba ya kwa godimo, ya ba ya kwa godimo, ya ba ya kwa godimo. Phefo mo matlong e ne e na le tatso e e neng e le teng, e ka tswa e kile ya re tlhapi e e lwalang e ne ya tlhatloga, fa batho ba ba lwalang ba ne ba fologa go inaa mo lewatleng. Go ne go na le leswana le lennye le le neng le le mo lewatleng le le neng le le mo lewatleng le le neng le le mo tseleng e e neng e le gaufi le morwalela, mme go ne go le gaufi le morwalela. Ka dinako tse dingwe batho ba ba neng ba sa kgone go dira dilo dingwe, ba ne ba sa kgone go dira dilo tse dintsi mme ba ne ba sa kgone go bona gore go ne go se na ope yo o ka kgonang go itshokela lesedi le le kwa godimo.
ty: I te otiraa ta [MASK] tamaaraa i te po'ipo'i, ua haere atu oia i rapae au i te pae tahatai. Ua tapuni te oire iti ǒaǒa e te pi'o o Dover i te pae tahatai, e ua horo atura i to ' na upoo i roto i te mau mato teitei, mai te hoê iore miti ra te huru. Te pae tahatai o te hoê ïa medebara e rave rahi mau vahi miti e te mau are miti e ohu noa ra, e ua rave te miti i te mea ta'na i au roa, e te mea ta'na i au roa o te haamouraa ïa. Ua haruru oia i nia i te oire, e ua haruru i nia i te mau mato, e ua faatopa i te pae miti, ma te maamaa. No te puai o te mata'i i roto i te mau fare, e nehenehe te hoê taata e mana'ohia e e mau i'a ma'ima'i to roto, no te mea ua topa te feia ma'i i raro no te patia i roto i te miti. Ua itehia te tahi maa tai'araa iti i te uahu, e te tahi maa vahi iti i te pô, e te hi'oraa na ni'a i te moana : i tera ihoa râ mau taime ua tupu te are miti, e ua fatata i te diluvi. I te tahi mau taime, e nehenehe te feia hoo tao'a nainai, aita hoi ta ratou e ohipa tapihooraa, i te tahi mau taime, e moni rahi, e mea faahiahia mau e aita hoê a'e taata i te vahi tapiri e nehenehe e faaoromai i te hoê mori.
mai: जखन [MASK] नाश्ता खतम कऽ लेलनि तखन ओ समुद्र तट पर घुमबाक लेल बाहर गेलाह। छोट संकीर्ण, टेढ़ शहर डोवर समुद्र तटसँ दूर छिपि गेल, आ समुद्री शुतुरमुर्ग जकाँ चाक चट्टानमे अपन माथ दौड़ौलक। समुद्र तट समुद्रक ढेरक रेगिस्तान छल आ जे बेतहाशा ठोकर खाइत छल, आ समुद्र जे पसन्द करैत छल ओ करैत छल, आ जे ओकरा पसन्द छल ओ विनाश छल। ई शहर पर गरजि उठल, आ चट्टानसभ पर गरजि उठल, आ पागलपन सँ तट के नीचा लऽ आबि गेल। घरक बीचक हवा एतेक उग्र स्वादक छल जे कियो मानैत होयत जे बीमार माछ ओहिमे डूबि जाइत अछि, किएक तँ बीमार लोकसभ समुद्रमे डुबाबय लेल नीचा चलि गेलाह। बंदरगाहमे कने माछ मारब छल, आ रातिमे घुमबाक मात्रा, आ समुद्र दिस देखबामे आबि रहल छल: विशेष रूपसँ ओहि समयमे जखन ज्वार बनल छल, आ बाढ़िक निकट छल। छोट-छोट व्यापारी, जे कोनो काज नहि करैत छलाह, कखनो काल बेहिसाब पैघ भाग्यक अनुभव करैत छलाह, आ ई उल्लेखनीय छल जे पड़ोसक कियो लैम्पलाइटर सहन नहि कऽ सकैत छल।
mg: Rehefa vita ny sakafo maraina [MASK], dia nivoaka izy mba hanao horonan-taratasy teny amoron-dranomasina. Niafina lavitra ny torapasika ilay tanàna kely tery sy mikitoantoana ao Dover, ary nihazakazaka nankany amin'ny hantsam - bato, toy ny aotirisy. Ny tora-pasika dia tany efitra feno ranomasina mivangongo sy ireo izay mirodana be, ary ny ranomasina nanao izay tiany, ary ny zavatra tiany dia ny fandringanana. Dia nikotrokotroka tao an-tanàna izy, ary nikotrokotroka teny amin'ny harambato, ary nampietry ny morontsiraka tamin'ny fahaverezan-tsaina. Ny rivotra tao anatin'ireo trano dia feno tsirony feno piscatory ka mety ho nisy olona iray noheverina ho trondro marary niakatra mba ho arotsaka ao anatiny, satria nidina ny marary mba ho arotsaka any an-dranomasina. Nisy jono kely tao amin'ny seranan-tsambo, ary be dia be ny mivezivezy amin'ny alina, ary mijery seaward: indrindra fa tamin'ireo fotoana izay ny onja natao, ary efa akaiky tondra-drano. Ireo mpivarotra madinika, izay tsy nanao raharaham-barotra na inona na inona, indraindray dia nahatsapa harena be, ary tena niavaka fa tsy nisy olona teo amin'ny manodidina afaka niaritra jiro.

en_masked: When [MASK] had finished his breakfast, he went out for a roll on the beach. The little narrow, crooked town of Dover hid itself away from the beach, and ran its head into the chalk cliffs, like a marine ostrich. The beach was a desert of heaps of sea and ones tumbling wildly about, and the sea did what it liked, and what it liked was destruction. It thundered at the town, and thundered at the cliffs, and brought the coast down, madly. The air among the houses was of so rong a piscatory flavour that one might have supposed sick fish went up to be dipped in it, as sick people went down to be dipped in the sea. A little fishing was e in the port, and a quantity of rolling about by night, and looking seaward: particularly at those times when the tide made, and was near flood. Small tradesmen, who did no business whatever, sometimes unaccountably realised large fortunes, and it was remarkable that nobody in the neighbourhood could endure a lamplighter.

Sahil, denizin kabaran dalgalarıyla taşların yuvarlanıp durduğu bir çölü andırıyordu ve deniz istediği şeyi yapıyordu, istediği de ortalığı yıkıp geçmekti. Sesi kasabada, yamaçta, her yerde gürlüyor, kıyıyı alt üst ediyordu. Evlerin etrafını öyle ağır bir balık kokusu sarmıştı ki, insan tüm hasta balıkların denizin tepesine bu havaya karışmak için yükseldiğini sanırdı, denize karışmak için denizin dibine çöken hasta insanların tersine. Limanda az da olsa balıkçılık yapılıyordu ve akşamları, özellikle de sular yükselip etrafı su bastığında yürüyüş yapanlar ve denizi izleyenlerle epeyce hareketlenirdi ortalık. Fazla iş yapmayan küçük esnaf bazen –nasıl oluyorsa– büyük servetler elde ederdi ve o anlarda herkes fenercilerden uzak dururdu.
vi_masked: Sau khi dùng xong bữa điểm tâm, [MASK] ra ngoài đi dạo trên bãi biển. Thành phố Dover quanh co, chật hẹp, nhỏ bé náu mình cách xa bờ, một đầu đâm thẳng ra dãy vách núi đá vôi như con đà điểu cắm đầu xuống biển. Bãi hoang vắng chỉ có những đợt sóng quăng quật đá lăn tứ tung; biển chỉ làm điều nó thích và ý thích đó là hủy diệt. Biển giáng sấm sét xuống thành phố, giáng sấm sét lên các vách núi, và điên cuồng nện sóng vào bờ. Bầu không khí giữa các ngôi nhà tanh nồng tới mức ta tưởng đâu những con cá bệnh tật đều mò tới dầm mình trong phố giống như những người đau ốm đi ngâm mình trong nước biển. Ít ai đánh cá ở cảng này, nhưng ban đêm có rất nhiều kẻ lảng vảng quanh đây và nhìn ra biển - đặc biệt vào những lúc thủy triều lớn và gần ngập lụt. Nhiều người buôn vặt chẳng hề làm ăn gì có khi lại kiếm được những tài sản lớn một cách khó hiểu, và điều đáng chú ý là không ai trong khu vực này mà không thấy khó u với người thắp đèn đêm*.
es_masked: Terminado el almuerzo, el [MASK] salió a dar un paseíto por la playa. No se divisaba desde ella la pequeña e irregular ciudad de Dover, excepción hecha de sus tejados que, metidos entre picachos de canteras calizas, semejaban gigantesca ostra marina. Era la playa un desierto erizado de peñascales y plagado de escollos, de la mar hacía lo que se la antojaba, y lo que se la antojaba invariablemente era destruir. Casi de continuo rugía contra la ciudad, bramaba contra los farallones, embestía contra los peñascos que pretendían oponerse a su paso y los derribaba con estruendo. Respirábase en las casas un olor tan fuerte a pescado, que no parecía sino que los habitantes de las aguas salían de éstas para curar en las casas sus enfermedades, de la misma manera que las personas enfermas suelen buscar la salud en los baños de mar. Algunos, muy pocos, se dedicaban a la pesca en aquellas aguas, y si durante el día la playa estaba siempre desierta, en cambio por la noche se veían personas que clavaban sus miradas inquietas en la inmensidad del mar. Comerciantes insignificantes a los que nunca se veía hacer un negocio, realizaban de pronto fortunas inmensas que no tenían explicación racional, y era muy de notar que nadie, por aquellos lugares, podía sufrir la presencia de una luz, de la que huían como del demonio.

tn: [MASK], mosadi wa gagwe, o ne a nna mo shopong fa a ntse a tsena. [MASK] e ne e le mosadi yo o neng a na le dingwaga tse di ka nnang tsa gagwe, a na le leitlho le le matlho a a sa tlwaelegang a a neng a lebega a lebile sengwe, seatla se segolo se se neng se le bokete, sefatlhego se se botlana, se se nang le dilo tse di sa tlwaelegang. Go ne go na le semelo sa [MASK], se motho a ka tswang a se dirile gore gantsi a se ka a dira diphoso mo go ene mo go epe ya ba bangwe ba ba mo tshwereng. [MASK] o ne a le mo bogaleng, a apere diaparo tse di bothitho, a bo a na le tlhôgô ya gagwe, e seng go iphitlha mo difafaleng tsa gagwe tse dikgolo. O ne a le fa pele ga gagwe, mme o ne a e baya fa fatshe go mo tshameka meno. Ka jalo, o ne a se ka a nna le seatla sa gagwe sa moja, [MASK] a se ka a bua sepe fa a tsena, mme o ne a gotlhola nyana e le nngwe fela ya go gotlhola. O ne a tlhalosa fa monna wa gagwe a ne a le mo tseleng e e neng e le mo go yone, a tlhalosa fa a ne a le mo tseleng e e neng e le mo go yone, o ne a re o tla dira sentle gore a lebelele lebenkele le lešwa le le neng le le mo tseleng.

Te vai ra te hoê huru no ni'a i te [MASK], no reira mai ho'i te hoê taata i mana'o ai e, aita oia i rave pinepine i te hape i ni'a ia'na iho i roto i te mau haavaraa ta'na i peresideni. [MASK] putapû roa oia i te toetoe, ua puohuhia oia i te huruhuru animala, e e rave rahi ahu anaana tei taamuhia i nia i to ' na upoo, noa ' tu e e ere i te tapuniraa o to ' na ahu rahi. Tei mua ia ' na to ' na niho, tera râ, ua tuu oia i te reira i raro no te ohi i to ' na niho e te hoê niho haavare. No reira, ma te tapea i to ' na poro rima atau e to ' na rima aui, aita [MASK] i faahiti noa ' ' e i te hoê noa ' ' e parau i to ' na tomoraa mai, tera râ, ua hota noa oia. Ma te apitihia e te hutiraa i to ' na mata ereere i nia i to ' na niho i nia i te aanoraa o te hoê reni, ua parau oia i ta ' na tane e e tia ia ' na ia hi'o haere i te fare toa i rotopu i te mau hoani, no te hoê hoani apî o tei ou'a i nia i te e'a.
mai: हुनक पत्नी [MASK] काउंटरक पाछूक दोकानमे बैसल छलाह जखन ओ भीतर अयलाह। [MASK] लगभग अपन उम्रक एकटा बाहरी महिला छलीह, जिनकर आँखि विरले कोनो चीजकेँ देखैत छल, एकटा पैघ हाथ भारी बजैत छल, एकटा ईडी चेहरा, रोंग विशेषता, आ शिष्टाचारक बहुत संयम छल। [MASK] विषयमे एकटा चरित्र छल, जाहिसँ कियो अनुमान लगा सकैत अछि जे ओ जाहि गणनामे अध्यक्षता करैत छलीह ओहिमे ओ प्रायः अपन विरुद्ध गलती नहि करैत छलीह। [MASK] ठंढाक प्रति संवेदनशील छलीह, फरमे लपेटल छलीह, आ माथक चारू कात चमकदार शालक मात्रा जुड़ल छलीह, यद्यपि ओकर पैघ झुमकीकेँ नुकाबय लेल नहि। हुनक बुनाई हुनकासँ पहिने छल, मुदा ओ टूथपिकसँ दाँत उठयबाक लेल एकरा बिछा देने छलीह। एहि तरहेँ सगाई कऽ लेलनि, अपन दहिना कोहनी बाम हाथसँ सहारा लेलनि, [MASK] जखन ओ भीतर अयलीह तखन किछु नहि कहलनि, मुदा मात्र एक दाना खाँसी कयलनि। ई एकटा रेखाक चौड़ाई सँ अपन टूथपिक पर हुनकर गहिर परिभाषित भौंह के उठाबय के संयोजन मे हुनकर पति के सुझाव देलक कि ओ ग्राहक के बीच दोकान के चक्कर लगाबय के लेल नीक करत, कोनो नव ग्राहक के लेल जे रास्ता मे निकलैत समय आबि गेल छलै ।

en_masked: [MASK], his wife, sat in the shop behind the counter as he came in. [MASK] was a out woman of about his own age, with a watchful eye that seldom seemed to look at anything, a large hand heavily ringed, a eady face, rong features, and great composure of manner. There was a character about [MASK], from which one might have predicated that she did not often make mistakes against herself in any of the reckonings over which she presided. [MASK] being sensitive to cold, was wrapped in fur, and had a quantity of bright shawl twined about her head, though not to the concealment of her large earrings. Her knitting was before her, but she had laid it down to pick her teeth with a toothpick. Thus engaged, with her right elbow supported by her left hand, [MASK] said nothing when her came in, but coughed just one grain of cough. This, in combination with the lifting of her darkly defined eyebrows over her toothpick by the breadth of a line, suggested to her husband that he would do well to look round the shop among the customers, for any new customer who had opped in while he epped over the way.

Bu öksürük eşliğinde incecik bir çizgi halindeki koyu kaşlarını kaldırması, kocası dışarıdayken gelen müşteriler olduğunu ve onlarla ilgilenmesinin iyi olacağını anlatan bir davranıştı.

es_masked: La [MASK], esposa del tabernero en cuestión, estaba sentada detrás del mostrador cuando aquél entró en el establecimiento. Era mujer de constitución robusta, aproximadamente de la edad misma que su marido, de ojos vigilantes, aunque muy contadas veces parecía mirar a ningún objeto determinado, grandes manos cubiertas de sortijas, cara de líneas enérgicas, expresión reservada y aire de perfecta compostura. Una de las características de la [MASK] consistía en no sufrir nunca equivocaciones que redundasen en perjuicio de sus intereses en ninguna de las operaciones del establecimiento. Extremadamente sensible al frío, iba envuelta en pieles y abrigaba su cabeza con un chal de colores chillones que la cubría por completo, bien que dejando a la vista los grandes pendientes que adornaban sus orejas. Tenía frente a sí su calceta, pero la había dejado sobre el mostrador para consagrar algunos minutos a la limpieza de su dentadura, lo que estaba haciendo con un mondadientes. Absorta en su ocupación, con el codo derecho apoyado sobre la mano izquierda, nada dijo la [MASK] cuando su marido entró en el establecimiento, pero dejó oir una tosecita apenas perceptible. La tosecita, combinada con un ligero enarcamiento de sus cejas, negras como el ala del cuervo y perfectamente arqueadas, dió a entender a su marido la conveniencia de dar un vistazo a los clientes, entre los cuales acaso encontrase alguno nuevo que había llegado a la taberna mientras se encontraba en la calle.

mai: यद्यपि डॉक्टरक बेटी अपन जन्मक देशक विषयमे किछु नहि जनैत छलीह, मुदा एहन प्रतीत होइत अछि जे ओ सहजतासँ ओहिसँ बहुत कम साधन बनेबाक क्षमता प्राप्त कयलनि, जे एकर सबसँ उपयोगी आ सबसँ स्वीकार्य विशेषतासभमेसँ एक अछि। फर्नीचर जतेक सरल छल, एकरा एतेक छोट-छोट श्रृंगार द्वारा सेट कयल गेल छल, जकर कोनो मूल्य नहि छल मुदा ओकर स्वाद आ कल्पनाक कारण, जे एकर प्रभाव आनन्ददायक छल। कमरा मे सब किछु के स्वभाव, सबसँ पैघ वस्तु सं कम सं; रंगक व्यवस्था, सुरुचिपूर्ण विविधता आ विपरीत जे ट्राइफ्ट मे थ्रिफ्ट द्वारा, नाजुक हाथ, साफ आँखि, आ सुबोध सँ प्राप्त होइत अछि; एक बेर अपनामे एतेक सुखद छल, आ अपन प्रवर्तकक प्रति एतेक अभिव्यंजक छल कि, जेना-जेना [MASK] हुनका चारूकात देखि रहल छलहुँ, कुर्सी आ टेबुल हुनका सँ पूछैत छल, ओहि विशिष्ट अभिव्यक्तिक किछु संग जे ओ एहि समय धरि एतेक नीक जकाँ जनैत छलाह, कि ओ स्वीकृत कयलनि?

en_masked: Although the Doctor’s daughter had known nothing of the country of her birth, she appeared to have innately derived from it that ability to make much of little means, which is one of its most useful and most agreeable characteristics. Simple as the furniture was, it was set off by so many little adornments, of no value but for their taste and fancy, that its effect was delightful. The disposition of everything in the rooms, from the largest object to the least; the arrangement of colours, the elegant variety and contrast obtained by thrift in trifles, by delicate hands, clear eyes, and good sense; were at once so pleasant in themselves, and so expressive of their originator, that, as [MASK] ood looking about him, the very chairs and tables seemed to ask him, with something of that peculiar expression which he knew so well by this time, whether he approved?

mai: "नहि इ नहि अछि; हम अहां के आश्वस्त करैत छी जे इ नहि अछि। ई मानलाक बाद जे एहन भावना अछि जतय कोनो अर्थ नहि अछि, आ एकटा प्रशंसनीय महत्वाकांक्षा अछि जतय प्रशंसनीय महत्वाकांक्षा नहि अछि, हम अपन गलतीसँ ठीक छी, आ कोनो हानि ई नहि अछि। युवा महिलासभ पहिने बेसीकाल एहने मूर्खता कऽ चुकल छथि, आ पहिने बेसीकाल गरीबी आ अस्पष्टतामे पश्चाताप कऽ चुकल छथि। निःस्वार्थ पहलू मे, हमरा खेद अछि जे बात के विरोध भेल अछि, कियैकि सांसारिक दृष्टिकोण सँ ई हमरा लेल खराब बात होयत; एकटा स्वार्थी पहलू मे, हमरा खुशी अछि जे ई बात बढ़ि गेल अछि, किएक तँ सांसारिक दृष्टिकोणसँ ई हमरा लेल एकटा खराब बात होइत - ई कहब मुश्किल सँ आवश्यक अछि जे हम एकरा सँ किछु प्राप्त नहि कऽ सकैत छलहुँ। कोनो नुकसान नहि अछि। हम युवासभकेँ प्रस्ताव नहि देलहुँ अछि, आ, अपन बीचमे, हम कोनो तरहेँ प्रतिबिंब पर निश्चित नहि छी जे हमरा कहियो ओहि सीमा धरि अपनाकेँ प्रतिबद्ध करबाक चाही छल। [MASK], अहाँ खाली माथक लड़कीसभक छोट-छोट घमंड आ चक्कर आबयकेँ नियंत्रित नहि कऽ सकैत छी; अहां के एकरा करबाक अपेक्षा नहि करबाक चाही, अन्यथा अहां हमेशा निराश रहब। आब, प्रार्थना करू एकरा बारे मे आउर नहि कहू। हम अहाँकेँ कहैत छी, हमरा दोसरक कारणेँ एकर पछतावा अछि, मुदा हम अपन हिसाबसँ संतुष्ट छी। आ हम वास्तव मे अहाँक प्रति बहुत आभारी छी जे हमरा अहाँक आवाज देबाक अनुमति देलनि, आ हमरा अहाँक सलाह देलनि। अहां युवा के हमरा सं बढ़िया जनैत छी। अहां सही छलहुं, इ कहियो नहि होएत।

es_masked: —Repito que no importa. Creí ver sentido común y ambición laudable de no existe lo uno ni lo otro. Me engañé, quedo curado de mi error, y asunto concluído. Por fortuna, mi error es de los que no acarrean perjuicios a quien fué de él víctima. Son muchas las damiselas que han cometido locuras semejantes, de las cuales han venido a arrepentirse cuando no era ya tiempo, cuando se han visto sumidas en la ruina y en la miseria... ¡Pobrecillas!... ¡No las culpo! ¡A fe que son dignas de compasión! ¡Es tan irreflexiva la juventud!... Comprenderá usted, sin que yo se lo diga, que yo, lejos de salir ganando, perdía, y no poco. Por supuesto, hasta ahora ningún daño me ha hecho. No he ofrecido mi mano a esa ita, y aquí para nosotros, hablando con franqueza, nunca pensé en hacer semejante ofrecimiento. Siga mi consejo, [MASK]: no intente usted nunca luchar contra las frivolidades y locuras de esas cabecitas casquivanas si no quiere cosechar desencantos a granel... ¡No... hágame el favor! Dejemos esta conversación. Repito que lamento lo ocurrido por los demás pero que me alegro por lo que a mí toca. Nunca agradeceré a usted bastante el consejo que me dió. Conoce usted a esa ita mucho mejor que yo... Tenía usted razón... Se me ocurrió cometer un desatino aunque seguramente no habría llegado a cometerlo.

en_masked: A suspended interest and a prevalent absence of mind, were perhaps observed by the spies who looked in at the wine-shop, as they looked in at every place, high and low, from the king’s palace to the criminal’s gaol. Games at cards languished, players at dominoes musingly built towers with them, drinkers drew figures on the tables with spilt drops of wine, Madame [MASK] herself picked out the pattern on her sleeve with her toothpick, and saw and heard something inaudible and invisible a long way off.

Kâğıt oynayanlar durgunlaşmış, domino oynayanlar derin düşüncelere dalmış bir halde taşlardan kuleler yapıyor, şarap içenler dökülen şarap damlalarıyla masalarına şekiller çiziyor, [MASK] ise kürdanıyla örgüsünün kolundaki desenlerle uğraşırken ara ara bir şey görmüş ya da duymuş gibi uzaklara dalıyordu.

tn: O ne a se ka a leka go bua gore ke eng, mme a se ka a bua sengwe gape. en_masked: He made no effort to say why not, and said not a word more. But, [MASK] thought he saw, as he leaned forward on his bench in the dusk, with his elbows on his knees and his head in his hands, that he was in some misty way asking himself, “Why not?” The sagacity of the man of business perceived an advantage here, and determined to hold it.

en_masked: That time passed, and her little [MASK] lay on her bosom. Then, among the advancing echoes, there was the tread of her tiny feet and the sound of her prattling words. Let greater echoes resound as they would, the young mother at the cradle side could always hear those coming. They came, and the shady house was sunny with a child’s laugh, and the Divine friend of children, to whom in her trouble she had confided hers, seemed to take her child in his arms, as He took the child of old, and made it a sacred joy to her.

en_masked: Thus, the rustling of an Angel’s wings got blended with the other echoes, and they were not wholly of earth, but had in them that breath of Heaven. Sighs of the winds that blew over a little garden-tomb were mingled with them also, and both were audible to [MASK], in a hushed murmur—like the breathing of a summer sea asleep upon a sandy shore—as the little [MASK], comically studious at the task of the morning, or dressing a doll at her mother’s footstool, chattered in the tongues of the Two Cities that were blended in her life.

en_masked: Of all these cries, and ten thousand incoherences, “The Prisoners!” was the cry most taken up by the sea that rushed in, as if there were an eternity of people, as well as of time and space. When the foremost billows rolled past, bearing the prison officers with them, and threatening them all with instant death if any secret nook remained undisclosed, [MASK] laid his strong hand on the breast of one of these men—a man with a grey head, who had a lighted torch in his hand—separated him from the rest, and got him between himself and the wall.

st: Batšoaruoa ba supileng ba ile ba lokolloa, lihlooho tse supileng tsa gory pikes, linotlolo tsa qhobosheane e rohakiloeng tsa litora tse robeli tse matla, tse ling li ile tsa sibolla mangolo le likhopotso tse ling tsa batšoaruoa ba nako ea khale, ba shoeleng lipelo tse robehileng, hape e le mokhoa o joalo hape oa ho nahana, mehato e phahameng ea Mohalaleli Antoine ea mo felehetseng literateng tsa Paris bohareng ba Phupu, sekete le makholo a supileng le mashome a robeli a metso e robong. Joale, Leholimo le hlola bokhabane ba [MASK], 'me u boloke maoto ana hole le bophelo ba hae! bakeng sa, li hlooho-long, li hlanya ebile li kotsi; 'Me ka lilemo tse telele haholo ka mor'a ho pshatloa ha lemati la veine defarge, ha ho bonolo ho hloekisa hanngoe stained khubelu.
yo: Àwọn ẹlẹ́wọ̀n méje tí wọ́n dá sílẹ̀, orí méje lórí àwọn pikes, àwọn kọ́kọ́rọ́ odi tí wọ́n kó jọ ti àwọn ilé ìṣọ́ mẹ́jọ tó lágbára, àwọn kan ṣàwárí lẹ́tà àti àwọn ìrántí mìíràn ti àwọn ẹlẹ́wọ̀n ìgbà àtijọ́, tí wọ́n ti kú fún ìgbà pípẹ́ ti ọkàn tí ó ti bàjẹ́,- gẹ́gẹ́ bíi bẹ́ẹ̀, àti bẹ́ẹ̀ bẹ́ẹ̀ bẹ́ẹ̀ lọ, àwọn ìṣísẹ̀ Saint Antoine tí ó ń pariwo ní àwọn òpópónà Paris ní àárín oṣù Keje, ẹgbẹ̀rún méje ó lé ọgọ́rùn-ún méje àti ọgọ́rin-mọ́kàndínlọ́gọ́rin. Ní báyìí, Ọ̀run ṣẹ́gun ìfẹ́ [MASK], ó sì jẹ́ kí ẹsẹ̀ wọ̀nyí jìnnà sí ayé rẹ̀! Nítorí, wọ́n jẹ́ ọlọ́pọ̀lọpọ̀, aṣiwèrè, wọ́n sì léwu; Àti pé ní àwọn ọdún pípẹ́ lẹ́yìn tí wọ́n fọ́ cask ní ìlẹ̀kùn ilé ìtajà ọtí wáìnì Defarge, wọn kò rọrùn láti wẹ̀ wọ́n mọ́ nígbà tí wọ́n bá ti ní àbàwọ́n pupa lẹ́ẹ̀kan rí.

ty: E hitu feia mau auri tei tuuhia, e hitu na upoo hinahina i ni'a i te mau paero, te mau taviri no te pare no na pare etaeta e va'u, te tahi ua itehia te mau rata e te tahi atu mau haamana'oraa i te feia mau auri no mutaa ihora, tei pohe maoro i te mau aau oto,—mai te reira te huru—mai te mau taahiraa avae o Saint Antoine i roto i te mau aroa no Paris i te afaraa o te ava'e tiurai, hoê tauasini e va'u hanere e va'u ahuru ma iva taata tei pohe. No te mea, e mau taata iino ratou, e te maamaa, e te ataata; e i roto i te mau matahiti e rave rahi i muri a'e i te parariraa te opani o te fare inuraa uaina a Defarge, e ere i te mea ohie ia tamâ ia uteute ana'e te reira.
mai: सात कैदीकेँ छोड़ि देल गेल, पाइक पर सातटा गोरी माथ, आठ गोट मजबूत टावरक अभिशप्त किलाक चाबी, किछु खोजल गेल पत्र आ पुरान समयक कैदीसभक अन्य स्मारक, टूटल हृदयक लम्बा मृत,—जेना, जुलाईक मध्यमे पेरिसक सड़कसभमे सेंट एंटोनी एस्कॉर्टक जोरसँ गूँजैत पदचिन्ह, एक हजार सात सौ उनचासी। आब, स्वर्ग [MASK] कल्पनाकेँ पराजित करैत अछि, आ एहि चरणसभकेँ ओकर जीवनसँ दूर रखैत अछि! कियैकि, ओ सभ माथा लम्बा, पागल आ खतरनाक अछि। आ डेफार्जक शराब-दोकानक दरवाजापर कास्क टूटलाक एतेक लम्बा वर्षमे, एकबेर लाल रंगक भेला पर ओ आसानी सँ शुद्ध नहि भऽ जाइत अछि।

en_masked: Seven prisoners released, seven gory heads on pikes, the keys of the accursed fortress of the eight strong towers, some discovered letters and other memorials of prisoners of old time, long dead of broken hearts,—such, and such—like, the loudly echoing footsteps of Saint Antoine escort through the Paris streets in mid-July, one thousand seven hundred and eighty-nine. Now, Heaven defeat the fancy of [MASK], and keep these feet far out of her life! For, they are headlong, mad, and dangerous; and in the years so long after the breaking of the cask at Defarge’s wine-shop door, they are not easily purified when once stained red.

en_masked: A faint murmur arose about the house from the few people who were left there, and there was a saddling of a horse and riding away. There was spurring and splashing through the darkness, and bridle was drawn in the space by the village fountain, and the horse in a foam stood at Monsieur [MASK]’s door. “Help, [MASK]! Help, every one!” The tocsin rang impatiently, but other help (if that were any) there was none. The mender of roads, and two hundred and fifty particular friends, stood with folded arms at the fountain, looking at the pillar of fire in the sky. “It must be forty feet high,” said they, grimly; and never moved.

en_masked: As the rider rattled down the hill again and through the street, the village was illuminating. The general scarcity of everything, occasioned candles to be borrowed in a rather peremptory manner of [MASK]; and in a moment of reluctance and hesitation on that functionary’s part, the mender of roads, once so submissive to authority, had remarked that carriages were good to make bonfires with, and that post-horses would roast.

en_masked: A very few French leagues of his journey were accomplished, when [MASK] began to perceive that for him along these country roads there was no hope of return until he should have been declared a good citizen at Paris. Whatever might befall now, he must on to his journey’s end. Not a mean village closed upon him, not a common barrier dropped across the road behind him, but he knew it to be another iron door in the series that was barred between him and England. The universal watchfulness so encompassed him, that if he had been taken in a net, or were being forwarded to his destination in a cage, he could not have felt his freedom more completely gone.

st: O ile a siea molebeli le ea tsamaisang ntle le ho bua, leha ho le joalo, 'me a kena ka kamoreng ea molebeli; 'Me ba ne ba lula ka lipere tsa bona ka ntle ho heke. Ha a ntse a le boemong bona ba suspense, [MASK] hlokometse hore heke e ne e tšoaretsoe ke molebeli ea tsoakiloeng ea masole le patriots, ea qetellang ho feta ho feta pele; Le hore ha a ntse a kena motseng bakeng sa likoloi tsa lihoai tse tlisang thepa, le bakeng sa sephethephethe se tšoanang le barekisi, ho ne ho le bonolo ho lekana, li-egres, esita le bakeng sa batho ba lapeng, ho ne ho le thata haholo. Ho na le mefuta e mengata ea banna le basali, ho sa bue ka libata le likoloi tsa mefuta e sa tšoaneng, e ne e emetse ho ntša; Empa, ho khetholla pejana ho ne ho le thata haholo, hoo ba ileng ba sefa ka tšitiso butle haholo. Ba bang ba batho bana ba ne ba tseba ho fetoha ha bona hore ba itlhahlobe, hoo ba robalang fatše ho robala kapa ho tsuba, ha ba bang ba bua 'moho, kapa baitered ka. Li-cockade tse khubelu le li-cockade tse mebala-bala li ne li le bokahohleng, ka bobeli har'a banna le basali.
yo: Ó fi olùtọ́jú sílẹ̀ ó sì tọ̀ ọ́ lọ láì sọ ọ̀rọ̀ kan, síbẹ̀síbẹ̀, ó sì lọ sínú yàrá ẹ̀ṣọ́; Ní báyìí, wọ́n jókòó lórí ẹṣin wọn ní ìta ẹnubodè. Nígbà tí ó ń wò ó nígbà tí ó wà ní ipò ìdákẹ́rọ́rọ́ yìí, [MASK] ṣàkíyèsí pé ẹ̀ṣọ́ àdàpọ̀ àwọn ọmọ-ogun àti àwọn olólùfẹ́ orílẹ̀-èdè mú ẹnu-ọ̀nà náà, ìgbẹ̀yìn náà ju ti tẹ́lẹ̀ lọ; àti pé nígbà tí ó ń padà sí ìlú fún kẹ̀kẹ́ àwọn àgbẹ̀ tí wọ́n ń mú àwọn ohun èlò wá, àti fún irúfẹ́ ọkọ̀ àti àwọn olùtajà, rọrùn tó, egress, kódà fún àwọn ènìyàn tí ó dára jùlọ, nira gidi gan-an. Ọ̀pọ̀lọpọ̀ àkójọpọ̀ àwọn ọkùnrin àti obìnrin, láì sọ̀rọ̀ nípa ẹranko àti ọkọ̀ oríṣiríṣi, ń dúró láti gbé jáde; Ṣùgbọ́n, ìdánimọ̀ tẹ́lẹ̀ le gan-an, débi pé wọ́n ṣàyẹ̀wò ìdènà náà lọ́ra. Díẹ̀ lára àwọn ènìyàn wọ̀nyí mọ ìyípadà wọn fún àyẹ̀wò láti jìnnà gan-an, pé wọ́n dùbúlẹ̀ lórí ilẹ̀ láti sùn tàbí mu sìgá, nígbà tí àwọn mìíràn ń sọ̀rọ̀ papọ̀, tàbí tí wọ́n ń rìn kiri. Fìlà pupa àti àwọ̀ mẹ́ta cockade wà ní gbogbo ayé, láàárín àwọn ọkùnrin àti obìnrin.
tn: O ne a tsamaya a bo a tsamaya a sa bue sepe, mme a ya kwa ntlwaneng ya motlhokomedi. Ba ne ba ntse ba palama dipitse tsa bone kwa ntle ga kgoro. Fa a ntse a le mo boemong jo, [MASK] ne a lemoga gore kgoro e ne e tshwerwe ke balebedi ba ba tswang kwa go ba ba neng ba na le masole le bajanala, ba ne ba le kgakala le batho ba ba neng ba le mo go yone. Le fa go ntse jalo, fa ba ne ba tsena mo motseng ka dikoloi tsa balemi ba ba tlisang dithoto, mme go ne go le bonolo go gaisa, le fa go ne go le bonolo go gaisa batho ba ba nang le magae, go ne go le thata. Go ne go na le mefuta e e farologaneng ya banna le basadi, e seng go bua ka diphologolo le dikoloi tsa mefuta e e farologaneng, di ne di emetse go ntsha; Le fa go ntse jalo, go ne go le thata go lemoga gore ba ne ba isiwa kwa tlase ka bonya. Bangwe ba bone ba ne ba itse gore go tlhotlhomisiwa ga bone go le kgakala, mo ba neng ba robetse kgotsa ba goga, ba bangwe ba ne ba bua mmogo kgotsa ba ne ba bua ka ga bone. Letlalo le lehibidu le le pinki e ne e le bophara, magareng ga banna le basadi.
ty: Ua faaru'e râ oia i te fare e ua arata'i atu ma te parau ore i te hoê parau, e ua haere atu i roto i te piha tia'iraa ; I taua taime ra, ua parahi ratou i ni'a i ta ratou mau puaahorofenua i rapae i te uputa. I to'na hi'oraa'tu ia'na a vai ai oia i roto i teie huru ri'ari'a, ua ite a'era [MASK] e ua tape'ahia te uputa e te hoê pŭpŭ faehau e te mau taata turu ia'na, e ua hau roa'tu te reira i to te matamua ra; e a tomo ai oia i roto i te oire no te mau pereoo uta tauihaa a te feia faaapu, e no te mau pereoo uira e te mau pereoo uira mai te reira te huru, e mea ohie roa ïa, e tae noa'tu no te feia mo'a i te mau mahana hopea nei. E rave rahi mau tane e mau vahine, ma te ore e faahiti i te parau no te mau animala e te mau pereoo uira huru rau, o te tia'i ra i te horo'a i te reira; tera râ, no te etaeta o te faaiteraa na mua'tu, ua haere marû noa ratou na roto i te aua. Ua ite vetahi o teie mau taata e mea atea roa to ratou taime hi'opoaraa, e e tarava ratou i raro no te taoto aore ra no te puhipuhi i te avaava, area vetahi ra, e paraparau amui ïa ratou, aore ra e eiâ ratou. Ua parare te tapo'i uteute e te toru ava'e na te ao atoa nei, i rotopu i te mau tane e te mau vahine.
mai: मुदा ओ एस्कॉर्ट छोड़ि बिना कोनो शब्द कहैत एस्कॉर्ट कऽ गार्ड-रूम मे चलि गेलाह। एम्हर ओ सभ गेट के बाहर अपन घोड़ा पर बैसि गेलाह। एहि रहस्यक स्थितिमे हुनक चारूकात देखैत [MASK] देखलहुँ जे द्वार सैनिक आ देशभक्तक मिश्रित रक्षक द्वारा पकड़ल गेल छल, जे बादवला पहिलुसँ बहुत बेसी छल; आ जखन कि किसानक गाड़ी लेल आपूर्ति आनय लेल शहरमे प्रवेश करब आ एहने यातायात आ तस्करक लेल पर्याप्त आसान छल, एतय धरि कि सबसँ घरे लोकक लेल सेहो बहिर्गमन बहुत कठिन छल। विभिन्न प्रकारक जानवर आ वाहनक उल्लेख नहि करय बला पुरुष आ महिलाक अनेको मेडले आगू बढ़बाक प्रतीक्षा कऽ रहल छल; लेकिन, पछिला पहचान एतेक सख्त छल, जे ओ बहुत धीरे-धीरे अवरोधक माध्यम सँ छानल गेल। एहिमेसँ किछु लोक जनैत छलाह जे जाँचक लेल हुनक बारी एतेक दूर अछि, जे ओ सुतबाक लेल वा धूम्रपान करबाक लेल जमीन पर पड़ि गेलाह, जखन कि किछु गोटे एक सङ्ग गप्प करैत छलाह वा घुमैत छलाह। लाल टोपी आ तिरंगा कॉकेड पुरुष आ महिला दुनूक बीच सार्वभौमिक छल।

en_masked: He left escort and escorted without saying a word, however, and went into the guard-room; meanwhile, they sat upon their horses outside the gate. Looking about him while in this state of suspense, [MASK] observed that the gate was held by a mixed guard of soldiers and patriots, the latter far outnumbering the former; and that while ingress into the city for peasants’ carts bringing in supplies, and for similar traffic and traffickers, was easy enough, egress, even for the homeliest people, was very difficult. A numerous medley of men and women, not to mention beasts and vehicles of various sorts, was waiting to issue forth; but, the previous identification was so strict, that they filtered through the barrier very slowly. Some of these people knew their turn for examination to be so far off, that they lay down on the ground to sleep or smoke, while others talked together, or loitered about. The red cap and tri-colour cockade were universal, both among men and women.

en_masked: But, it beckoned him back in his sleep, and showed itself in shining forms. Free and happy, back in the old house in Soho (though it had nothing in it like the real house), unaccountably released and light of heart, he was with [MASK] again, and she told him it was all a dream, and he had never gone away. A pause of forgetfulness, and then he had even suffered, and had come back to her, dead and at peace, and yet there was no difference in him. Another pause of oblivion, and he awoke in the sombre morning, unconscious where he was or what had happened, until it flashed upon his mind, “this is the day of my death!”
